fields.description: Main category for Models and Algorithms

fields.name: Datasets
fields.description: Main category for Datasets

fields.name: Code Related
fields.description: Main category for Code and Reproducibility

fields.name: Experimental Results
fields.description: Main category for Experimental Results

fields.name: Model/Algorithm Description
fields.description: A description of the mathematical setting, algorithm, and/or model.

fields.name: Assumptions
fields.description: An explanation of any assumptions.

fields.name: Software Framework
fields.description: A declaration of what software framework and version you used.

fields.name: Statistics
fields.description: The relevant statistics, such as the number of examples.

fields.name: Study Cohort
fields.description: Description of the study cohort.

fields.name: Existing Datasets Info
fields.description: For existing datasets, citations as well as descriptions if they are not publicly available.

fields.name: Data Collection Process
fields.description: For new data collected, a complete description of the data collection process, such as descriptions of the experimental setup, device(s) used, image acquisition parameters, subjects/objects involved, instructions to annotators, and methods for quality control.

fields.name: Download Link
fields.description: A link to a downloadable version of the dataset (if public).

fields.name: Ethics Approval
fields.description: Whether ethics approval was necessary for the data.

fields.name: Dependencies
fields.description: Specification of dependencies.

fields.name: Training Code
fields.description: Training code.

fields.name: Evaluation Code
fields.description: Evaluation code.

fields.name: Pre-trained Models
fields.description: (Pre-)trained model(s).

fields.name: Dataset for Code
fields.description: Dataset or link to the dataset needed to run the code.

fields.name: README & Results
fields.description: README file including a table of results accompanied by precise commands to run to produce those results.

fields.name: Hyperparameters
fields.description: The range of hyperparameters considered, the method to select the best hyperparameter configuration, and the specification of all hyperparameters used to generate results.

fields.name: Sensitivity Analysis
fields.description: Information on sensitivity regarding parameter changes.

fields.name: Training/Eval Runs
fields.description: The exact number of training and evaluation runs.

fields.name: Baseline Methods
fields.description: Details on how baseline methods were implemented and tuned.

fields.name: Data Splits
fields.description: The details of training / validation / testing splits.

fields.name: Evaluation Metrics
fields.description: A clear definition of the specific evaluation metrics and/or statistics used to report results.

fields.name: Central Tendency & Variation
fields.description: A description of results with central tendency (e.g., mean) & variation (e.g., error bars).

fields.name: Statistical Significance
fields.description: An analysis of the statistical significance of reported differences in performance between methods.

fields.name: Runtime / Energy Cost
fields.description: The average runtime for each result, or estimated energy cost.

fields.name: Memory Footprint
fields.description: A description of the memory footprint.

fields.name: Failure Analysis
fields.description: An analysis of situations in which the method failed.

fields.name: Computing Infrastructure
fields.description: A description of the computing infrastructure used (hardware and software).

fields.name: Clinical Significance
fields.description: Discussion of clinical significance.
